  "text": "Suppression of RNA silencing. To assess the ability of C4 proteins to suppress PTGS, A. tumefaciens strain C58C1 cultures harbouring pBin438-TYLCCNVC4 or pBin438-Y194C4 were infiltrated into N. benthamiana line 16c plants as described previously [CITATION_1] . A plasmid for the expression of the TEV HC-Pro gene under the control of the CaMV 35S promoter (p35S-HC-Pro) and the empty vector pBin438 were used as positive and negative controls, respectively.",
